{"pageProps":{"note":{"id":"rKL0p5CPTbP8562FTO8Mr","title":"Lec 6","desc":"","updated":1643713763645,"created":1643270579021,"custom":{},"fname":"acads.sem-6.computer-vision.lec-6","type":"note","vault":{"fsPath":"vault"},"contentHash":"28c588aa5c5862bbbdf55449e733344f","links":[],"anchors":{"thresholding":{"type":"header","text":"Thresholding","value":"thresholding","line":7,"column":0,"depth":1},"hysteresis-thresholding":{"type":"header","text":"Hysteresis Thresholding","value":"hysteresis-thresholding","line":13,"column":0,"depth":2},"implementation":{"type":"header","text":"Implementation","value":"implementation","line":21,"column":0,"depth":3},"edge-detection-using-second-derivative":{"type":"header","text":"Edge Detection using Second Derivative","value":"edge-detection-using-second-derivative","line":27,"column":0,"depth":1},"discrete-lapacian-operator":{"type":"header","text":"Discrete lapacian operator","value":"discrete-lapacian-operator","line":40,"column":0,"depth":2},"implementation-1":{"type":"header","text":"Implementation","value":"implementation-1","line":50,"column":0,"depth":3},"effect-of-noise":{"type":"header","text":"Effect of noise","value":"effect-of-noise","line":59,"column":0,"depth":1}},"children":[],"parent":"ZnnjqzTxyepMvwsX6Lytr","data":{}},"body":"<h1 id=\"lec-6\">Lec 6<a aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"anchor-heading icon-link\" href=\"#lec-6\"></a></h1>\n<h1 id=\"thresholding\">Thresholding<a aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"anchor-heading icon-link\" href=\"#thresholding\"></a></h1>\n<ul>\n<li><img src=\"/notes/assets/images/2022-01-30-15-52-25.png\"></li>\n<li>thresholding helps us to get a sharper edge and get a better idea of shape</li>\n<li>a simple approach would be to fix a bound and perform binary classification(edge, non-edge)</li>\n</ul>\n<h2 id=\"hysteresis-thresholding\">Hysteresis Thresholding<a aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"anchor-heading icon-link\" href=\"#hysteresis-thresholding\"></a></h2>\n<ul>\n<li>if the gradient at a pixel is:\n<ul>\n<li>above <em>high threshold</em> <span class=\"math math-inline\"><span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><msub><mi>T</mi><mi>h</mi></msub></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">T_h</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class=\"katex-html\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.8333em;vertical-align:-0.15em;\"></span><span class=\"mord\"><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.13889em;\">T</span><span class=\"msupsub\"><span class=\"vlist-t vlist-t2\"><span class=\"vlist-r\"><span class=\"vlist\" style=\"height:0.3361em;\"><span style=\"top:-2.55em;margin-left:-0.1389em;margin-right:0.05em;\"><span class=\"pstrut\" style=\"height:2.7em;\"></span><span class=\"sizing reset-size6 size3 mtight\"><span class=\"mord mathnormal mtight\">h</span></span></span></span><span class=\"vlist-s\">​</span></span><span class=\"vlist-r\"><span class=\"vlist\" style=\"height:0.15em;\"><span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span>, classify it as <strong>edge</strong></li>\n<li>below <em>low threshold</em> <span class=\"math math-inline\"><span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><msub><mi>T</mi><mi>l</mi></msub></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">T_l</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class=\"katex-html\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.8333em;vertical-align:-0.15em;\"></span><span class=\"mord\"><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.13889em;\">T</span><span class=\"msupsub\"><span class=\"vlist-t vlist-t2\"><span class=\"vlist-r\"><span class=\"vlist\" style=\"height:0.3361em;\"><span style=\"top:-2.55em;margin-left:-0.1389em;margin-right:0.05em;\"><span class=\"pstrut\" style=\"height:2.7em;\"></span><span class=\"sizing reset-size6 size3 mtight\"><span class=\"mord mathnormal mtight\" style=\"margin-right:0.01968em;\">l</span></span></span></span><span class=\"vlist-s\">​</span></span><span class=\"vlist-r\"><span class=\"vlist\" style=\"height:0.15em;\"><span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span>, classify it as <strong>non-edge</strong></li>\n<li>for any pixel in between\n<ul>\n<li>iteratively classify based on the neighbors</li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<h3 id=\"implementation\">Implementation<a aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"anchor-heading icon-link\" href=\"#implementation\"></a></h3>\n<ul>\n<li><span class=\"math math-inline\"><span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><msub><mi>T</mi><mi>h</mi></msub><mo>:</mo><msub><mi>T</mi><mi>l</mi></msub><mo>=</mo><mn>1</mn><mo>:</mo><mn>2</mn><mspace width=\"0.2845em\"></mspace><mi>o</mi><mi>r</mi><mn>1</mn><mo>:</mo><mn>3</mn></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">T_h:T_l = 1:2\\hspace{1mm}or1:3</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class=\"katex-html\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.8333em;vertical-align:-0.15em;\"></span><span class=\"mord\"><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.13889em;\">T</span><span class=\"msupsub\"><span class=\"vlist-t vlist-t2\"><span class=\"vlist-r\"><span class=\"vlist\" style=\"height:0.3361em;\"><span style=\"top:-2.55em;margin-left:-0.1389em;margin-right:0.05em;\"><span class=\"pstrut\" style=\"height:2.7em;\"></span><span class=\"sizing reset-size6 size3 mtight\"><span class=\"mord mathnormal mtight\">h</span></span></span></span><span class=\"vlist-s\">​</span></span><span class=\"vlist-r\"><span class=\"vlist\" style=\"height:0.15em;\"><span></span></span></span></span></span></span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2778em;\"></span><span class=\"mrel\">:</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2778em;\"></span></span><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.8333em;vertical-align:-0.15em;\"></span><span class=\"mord\"><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.13889em;\">T</span><span class=\"msupsub\"><span class=\"vlist-t vlist-t2\"><span class=\"vlist-r\"><span class=\"vlist\" style=\"height:0.3361em;\"><span style=\"top:-2.55em;margin-left:-0.1389em;margin-right:0.05em;\"><span class=\"pstrut\" style=\"height:2.7em;\"></span><span class=\"sizing reset-size6 size3 mtight\"><span class=\"mord mathnormal mtight\" style=\"margin-right:0.01968em;\">l</span></span></span></span><span class=\"vlist-s\">​</span></span><span class=\"vlist-r\"><span class=\"vlist\" style=\"height:0.15em;\"><span></span></span></span></span></span></span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2778em;\"></span><span class=\"mrel\">=</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2778em;\"></span></span><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.6444em;\"></span><span class=\"mord\">1</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2778em;\"></span><span class=\"mrel\">:</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2778em;\"></span></span><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.6444em;\"></span><span class=\"mord\">2</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2845em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.02778em;\">or</span><span class=\"mord\">1</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2778em;\"></span><span class=\"mrel\">:</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2778em;\"></span></span><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.6444em;\"></span><span class=\"mord\">3</span></span></span></span></span></li>\n<li>select <span class=\"math math-inline\"><span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><msub><mi>T</mi><mi>h</mi></msub></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">T_h</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class=\"katex-html\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.8333em;vertical-align:-0.15em;\"></span><span class=\"mord\"><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.13889em;\">T</span><span class=\"msupsub\"><span class=\"vlist-t vlist-t2\"><span class=\"vlist-r\"><span class=\"vlist\" style=\"height:0.3361em;\"><span style=\"top:-2.55em;margin-left:-0.1389em;margin-right:0.05em;\"><span class=\"pstrut\" style=\"height:2.7em;\"></span><span class=\"sizing reset-size6 size3 mtight\"><span class=\"mord mathnormal mtight\">h</span></span></span></span><span class=\"vlist-s\">​</span></span><span class=\"vlist-r\"><span class=\"vlist\" style=\"height:0.15em;\"><span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span> such that edges cannot be ignored - <code style=\"background-color: #43b02a40; padding:3px 2px; border-radius: 5px\">seed points</code></li>\n<li>from the seed move to the <em>8-neighborhood</em> as long as the pixels does not fall below <span class=\"math math-inline\"><span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><msub><mi>T</mi><mi>l</mi></msub></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">T_l</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class=\"katex-html\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.8333em;vertical-align:-0.15em;\"></span><span class=\"mord\"><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.13889em;\">T</span><span class=\"msupsub\"><span class=\"vlist-t vlist-t2\"><span class=\"vlist-r\"><span class=\"vlist\" style=\"height:0.3361em;\"><span style=\"top:-2.55em;margin-left:-0.1389em;margin-right:0.05em;\"><span class=\"pstrut\" style=\"height:2.7em;\"></span><span class=\"sizing reset-size6 size3 mtight\"><span class=\"mord mathnormal mtight\" style=\"margin-right:0.01968em;\">l</span></span></span></span><span class=\"vlist-s\">​</span></span><span class=\"vlist-r\"><span class=\"vlist\" style=\"height:0.15em;\"><span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></li>\n</ul>\n<h1 id=\"edge-detection-using-second-derivative\">Edge Detection using Second Derivative<a aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"anchor-heading icon-link\" href=\"#edge-detection-using-second-derivative\"></a></h1>\n<details>\n<summary>edge derivative plots</summary>\n<p><img src=\"/notes/assets/images/2022-02-01-12-03-57.png\"></p>\n</details>\n<ul>\n<li>first derivative gives us the strength and direction</li>\n<li>second derivative is used to detect <em>polarity</em></li>\n<li><em>zero crossing</em> indicates the presence of edge and can locate thick edges</li>\n</ul>\n<h2 id=\"discrete-lapacian-operator\">Discrete lapacian operator<a aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"anchor-heading icon-link\" href=\"#discrete-lapacian-operator\"></a></h2>\n<ul>\n<li>finite differences of second order are given given by the <code style=\"background-color: #43b02a40; padding:3px 2px; border-radius: 5px\">del square</code> (<span class=\"math math-inline\"><span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><msub><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">∇</mi><mn>2</mn></msub><mi>I</mi></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">\\nabla_2 I</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class=\"katex-html\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.8333em;vertical-align:-0.15em;\"></span><span class=\"mord\"><span class=\"mord\">∇</span><span class=\"msupsub\"><span class=\"vlist-t vlist-t2\"><span class=\"vlist-r\"><span class=\"vlist\" style=\"height:0.3011em;\"><span style=\"top:-2.55em;margin-left:0em;margin-right:0.05em;\"><span class=\"pstrut\" style=\"height:2.7em;\"></span><span class=\"sizing reset-size6 size3 mtight\"><span class=\"mord mtight\">2</span></span></span></span><span class=\"vlist-s\">​</span></span><span class=\"vlist-r\"><span class=\"vlist\" style=\"height:0.15em;\"><span></span></span></span></span></span></span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.07847em;\">I</span></span></span></span></span>)\n<details>\n<summary>formulae for del-square</summary>\n</details></li>\n</ul>\n<p><img src=\"/notes/assets/images/2022-02-01-16-03-54.png\"></p>\n\n<h3 id=\"implementation-1\">Implementation<a aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"anchor-heading icon-link\" href=\"#implementation-1\"></a></h3>\n<ul>\n<li><img src=\"/notes/assets/images/2022-02-01-16-05-17.png\"></li>\n<li>this can be implemented using the convolution masks:</li>\n<li><img src=\"/notes/assets/images/2022-02-01-16-28-48.png\"></li>\n<li>when we appy this convolution masks, the convoluted matrix contains negative values\n<ul>\n<li>when plotting this image without normalising, we get an image where negative values give a blackish pixels, 0 gives greyish pixel and positive values gives brighter pixels</li>\n<li>therefore before plotting the final image, we need to normalize it to get a prope image</li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<h1 id=\"effect-of-noise\">Effect of noise<a aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"anchor-heading icon-link\" href=\"#effect-of-noise\"></a></h1>\n<p><img src=\"/notes/assets/images/2022-02-01-12-19-45.png\"></p>\n<ul>\n<li>if the noise increases, it becomes difficult to differentiate between noise and edge as the derivate detects rapid change</li>\n</ul>\n<br>\n<ul>\n<li>noise in the image is almost invisible </li>\n<li>but <em>difference filters</em> respond very strongly to noise</li>\n<li>noise changes the neighborhood and the outcome is very different</li>\n<li>solutions\n<ul>\n<li>if the frequency is high, remove using low pass filter</li>\n<li>use kernels of higher size to decrease noise sensitivity</li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n</ul>","noteIndex":{"id":"LBE6GBZjFtOaX27nwRSpq","title":"Notes 📚","desc":"","upda